ALL.description:
The Jishaku debug and diagnostic commands.

This command on its own gives a status brief.
All other functionality is within its subcommands.

ALL.description: Hides Jishaku from the help command.

Voice-related commands.

If invoked without subcommand, relays current voice state.

ALL.description: Disconnects from the voice channel in this guild, if there is one.

ALL.description: Adjusts the volume of an audio source if it is supported.

ALL.name: jishaku voice pause
ALL.description: Pauses a running audio source, if there is one.

ALL.name: jishaku voice play
ALL.description:
Plays audio direct from a URI.

Can be either a local file or an audio resource on the internet.

ALL.name: jishaku voice join
ALL.description:
Joins a voice channel, or moves to it if already connected.

Passing a voice channel uses that voice channel.
Passing a member will use that member's current voice channel.
Passing nothing will use the author's voice channel.

ALL.name: jishaku voice resume
ALL.description: Resumes a running audio source, if there is one.

ALL.name: jishaku voice youtube_dl
ALL.description: Plays audio from youtube_dl-compatible sources.

ALL.name: jishaku voice stop
ALL.description: Stops running an audio source, if there is one.

ALL.description: Shows Jishaku in the help command.

ALL.description: Logs this bot out.

ALL.name: jishaku tasks
ALL.description: Shows the currently running jishaku tasks.

ALL.name: jishaku cancel
ALL.description:
Cancels a task with the given index.

If the index passed is -1, will cancel the last task instead.

ALL.name: jishaku git
ALL.description: Shortcut for 'jsk sh git'. Invokes the system shell.

ALL.name: jishaku pip
ALL.description: Shortcut for 'jsk sh pip'. Invokes the system shell.

ALL.name: jishaku load
ALL.description:
Loads or reloads the given extension names.

Reports any extensions that failed to load.

ALL.name: jishaku node
ALL.description: Shortcut for scaffolding and executing 'npm run'. Only exists if the executables are detected.

ALL.name: jishaku unload
ALL.description:
Unloads the given extension names.

Reports any extensions that failed to unload.

ALL.name: jishaku repeat
ALL.description:
Runs a command multiple times in a row.

This acts like the command was invoked several times manually, so it obeys cooldowns.
You can use this in conjunction with `jsk sudo` to bypass this.

ALL.description:
Retrieve the invite URL for this bot.

If the names of permissions are provided, they are requested as part of the invite.

ALL.description:
Run a command with a different user, channel, or thread, optionally bypassing checks and cooldowns.

Users will try to resolve to a Member, but will use a User if it can't find one.

ALL.description: Run a command timing execution and catching exceptions.

ALL.description:

If a message contains `threshold` or more mentions then the
member will be automatically be punished.
The `threshold` must be greater than 3.

This only applies for user mentions. Everyone or Role
mentions are not included.
